_.py`\\n- `my-claw/tools/daemon.py`\\n- `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py`\\n- `tests/test_first_boot.py`\\n\\n## Correctness\\nThe `SilenceBudgetRule` (R10) correctly implements the per-voice accumulator math using the formula `rest_budget += (target_density - actual_density) * dt * k`. Enforcement at phrase boundaries accurately triggers either a breath extension (if an R6 breath is present) or a tacet-drop for the subsequent phrase when the budget exceeds the threshold.\\n\\n## Completeness\\nThe implementation is complete according to the spec. The rule handles:\\n- Accumulator math and budget tracking across multiple phrases.\\n- Breath extension path (R6 search and length doubling).\\n- Tacet-drop path (velocity zeroing and metadata marking).\\n- Budget reset after triggering.\\n- Role-gating (eligible roles only).\\n- Scaling via `k` parameter.\\n\\nThe test suite (17 new tests) provides exhaustive coverage for all these scenarios, including edge cases like single phrases or `k=0`.\\n\\n## Consistency\\nThe code follows established SenseWeave render rule patterns, including the use of frozen dataclasses, the `applies_to`/`apply` protocol, and the `role_is_eligible` filter. Integration into `render/rules/__init__.py` is correct.\\n\\n## Security\\nNo security vulnerabilities were introduced. The implementation is a pure-function transformation of tracker data.\\n\\n## Quality\\nCode quality is high, with clear separation of concerns in helper functions and comprehensive unit tests. The full repository test suite (2895 tests) passes, ensuring no regressions.\\n\\n## Issues Found\\n- [x] Minor: `pip install -e '.[dev]'` failed with `OSError: [Errno 1] Operation not permitted` on `/Users/anthony/.local/lib` due to macOS Seatbelt restrictions. This did not impact verification as all dependencies were already present and the test suite ran successfully.\\n\\n## Hardening Verification\\n- **`bootstrap_identity()` Startup Path:** Confirmed that `bootstrap_identity()` is invoked before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in both `my-claw/tools/daemon.py` (line 2462) and `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` (line 3542).\\n- **Identity Persistence:** `tests/test_first_boot.py` (TestStartupIdentityPersistence) verifies that identity is minted on first boot and persists across subsequent reboots.\\n\\n## Verdict: PASS\\n\\n## Notes for Lead Agent\\nThe implementation of the Silence Budget rule is robust and the test coverage is excellent. No further changes are required.\\n\"}}\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-010_20260408T223256Zc_1775694627.log:b3acaaa fix(startup): wire bootstrap_identity into daemon startup flow [T-008@20260408T223256Z]\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Zc_1777158076.log:- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: Startup hardening gap: `my-claw/tools/cypherclaw_daemon.py` does not call `bootstrap_identity()` before startup announcement and main loop, while this path is still part of the runnable daemon entry points (`my-claw/docs/PROJECT_GUIDE.md` and system scripts/tests reference it), so first-boot identity creation is not guaranteed in that mode. Severity: blocking..\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Zc_1777158076.log:my-claw/tools/daemon.py:102:from cypherclaw.first_boot import FirstBootAnnouncer, bootstrap_identity\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Zc_1777158076.log:specs/t-021@20260416t054258z-spec.md:23:   - Ensure `bootstrap_identity()` is correctly invoked before `FirstBootAnnouncer` in `cypherclaw_daemon.py`.\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Zc_1777158076.log:specs/t-021@20260416t054258z-spec.md:34:- Hardening checks around `bootstrap_identity` in `cypherclaw_daemon.py` must be addressed as mandated.\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Zc_1777158076.log:specs/t-021@20260416t054258z-spec.md:44:4. Startup hardening gap in `cypherclaw_daemon.py` is resolved (`bootstrap_identity()` called before announcement).\n./sdp/logs/Lead_T-013_20260425T183959Zc_1777158076.log:tests/test_governor_integration.py: