specific items to address]\n```\n\nCommit the verification report.\n\n## Candidate Hardening (Auto-Generated)\n\nUse the recurring failure patterns below as mandatory hardening checks:\n- Enforce behavioral regression tests before completion: **No tests for `GET /world/entities` — severity: blocking.** The acceptance criterion is not exercised. A `tests/test_narrative_api_entities.py` covering at minimum: (a) `domain=deniable` returns only deniable+shared; (b) no domain defaults to shared; (c) `type` filter; (d) pagination (`limit`, `offset`) must be added before this task is considered done..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: **Pagination may underdeliver under native-paginating stores — severity: minor.** If the backing store honours `limit`/`offset` natively but ignores `domain_filter`, post-filtering silently returns fewer than `limit` items per page. Consider fetching with a multiplier or delegating full pagination responsibility to the store..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: `domain=deniable` → only entities with `domain in {\"deniable\", \"shared\"}` returned..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: No `domain` param → only `domain=\"shared\"` entities returned..\n- Address this recurring failure mode explicitly: `type=character` filter narrows results..\n"}
