sdp/runner.log:1250:{"type":"tool_result","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:53:27.819Z","tool_id":"run_shell_command_1777683207732_0","status":"success","output":"commit 6028224477cfb9e1fa72bccccc873cf157e80a8a (HEAD -> feat/graceful-degradation)\nAuthor: Anthony Ainsworth <anthony@cascadiantech.com>\nDate:   Fri May 1 17:52:02 2026 -0700\n\n    feat(narrative-api): regression suite + auth gate [T-005@20260502T001347Z]\n    \n    - Add `auth_token` kwarg to `create_app(...)`: when set, every endpoint\n      requires matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401).\n      Empty/unset preserves auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull\n      and startup warning land cleanly on top.\n    - Pin the 4-scenario floor (success / auth failure when enabled / bad\n      input validation / downstream-engine error) for `POST /memory/search`,\n      `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback when the\n      deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent\n      and append-returns-None record synthesis.\n    - Coverage on `cypherclaw.narrative_api` is now 84%.\n\n CHANGELOG.md                         |   2 +\n specs/t-005@20260502t001347z-spec.md | 110 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/app.py  |  31 +++++++-\n tests/test_narrative_api_events.py   | 146 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py   | 112 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++\n 5 files changed, 398 insertions(+), 3 deletions(-)"}
sdp/runner.log:1288:{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":"2026-05-02T00:54:09.963Z","tool_name":"write_file","tool_id":"write_file_1777683249963_0","parameters":{"content":"# Verification Report — T-005@20260502T001347Z\n\n**Verify Agent:** gemini-3-flash-preview\n**Date:** 2026-05-02\n**Artifacts Reviewed:**\n- `src/cypherclaw/narrative_api/app.py`\n- `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py`\n- `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py`\n- `specs/t-005@20260502t001347z-spec.md`\n- `ESCALATIONS.md`\n\n## Correctness\nThe implementation correctly adds the `auth_token` parameter to `create_app` and implements the authentication gate using a FastAPI dependency. Every endpoint (`POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, `POST /events`) now requires the `X-Narrative-Auth` header when `auth_token` is configured. The test suite correctly exercises all four required scenarios (success, auth failure, bad input, downstream error) for each endpoint.\n\n## Completeness\nThe test suite is comprehensive:\n- **Success paths:** Covered for all endpoints, including domain filtering and checkpoint tailing.\n- **Auth failure:** Covered with missing and incorrect tokens returning 401.\n- **Bad input:** Covered via Pydantic validation (e.g., empty query, invalid limit) returning 422.\n- **Downstream error:** Covered by mocking store/searcher failures and simulating missing deploy-side packages (returning 502/503).\nCoverage on the `cypherclaw.narrative_api` module is 84%, exceeding the 80% requirement.\n\n## Consistency\nThe tests follow the project's convention of residing in the root `tests/` directory, which is correctly explained in the `ESCALATIONS.md` as a deviation from the task graph's deploy-side path to match the PromptClaw repo structure. The use of `RecordingEventStore` and `RecordingMemory` mocks is consistent with existing patterns.\n\n## Security\nThe authentication gate is implemented as a dependency that runs before the endpoint logic. While the comparison is a simple string match (as noted in the spec, T-010 owns the hardened comparison), it correctly secures the endpoints when a token is provided. No secrets were committed; the tests use placeholder \"secret\" strings.\n\n## Quality\nThe code is clean, well-documented, and passes all tests. Regression anchors (`test_first_boot.py`, `test_governor_integration.py`, etc.) remain green, ensuring no side effects on startup or resource management.\n\n## Issues Found\n- None.\n\n## Verdict: PASS\n\n## Notes for Lead Agent\nThe decision to keep tests in the root `tests/` directory to align with `pyproject.toml` is correct for this repository's layout. Coverage is solid, and the 503 fallback paths for missing deploy-side dependencies are well-tested.\n","file_path":"sdp/verification/t-005@20260502t001347z-verify.md"}}
