 - Added depth-2 capstone-engine end-to-end test coverage (frac-0062): `tests/test_capstone_engine.py` now includes `TestCapstoneCycleEndToEnd`, which drives the existing public `build_capstone_cycle()` API through complete EMSD capstone planning paths. The new tests verify all five canonical phases expose linked family, patch, arc, palette, mix, sampling, and DSP contracts; assert occupied Theramini routing activates the Conversation dialogue path and ducking behavior; assert away-practice late phases retarget sampling and DSP focus to `self_bus`; compare quiet cadences against occupied cycles for lower density and quieter mix targets; verify repertoire songs shape identity families, patches, imagery, and statement text; and round-trip phase diagnostics through `json.dumps`. `tests/test_capstone_engine_depth.py` pins the file's fractal depth at >= 2 (now `substantial (no tests)`, 9 real functions versus 2 trivial). Existing capstone assertions and `my-claw/tools/senseweave/capstone_engine.py` source behavior remain unchanged; startup identity anchors and the full validation gate (`4401 passed, 3 skipped`, Ruff clean, mypy clean) remain green.
